id: agent-recipe-compiler
title: Agent Recipe Compiler
version: 1.0.0
status: active
purpose: Compile agent run data into structured, versioned recipe artifacts that serve as reproducible, debuggable, and trainable records of how intelligence evolved.

requirements:
  - System must capture agent run data including model version, prompt version, memory version, retrieved documents, and reasoning patterns into structured recipe format
  - System must assign unique recipe IDs following pattern recipe-YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS
  - System must store evaluation scores with expert review status (none, cheap, expert)
  - System must track recipe outcomes as accepted, rejected, or needs_revision
  - System must index recipes in a local SQLite database with full-text search capability
  - System must expose recipes via a local HTTP API at /api/recipes
  - System must support recipe export to JSON and CSV formats for training data generation
  - System must detect recipe drift by comparing consecutive runs against baseline patterns
  - System must generate recipe summaries showing success rates, model performance, and memory usage
  - System must support recipe versioning with semantic versioning for prompt and memory changes
  - System must ensure all data remains local — no external API calls during recipe capture
  - System must validate recipe schema before storage using GBNF grammar constraints via Ollama

constraints:
  - All recipe data must be stored locally in SQLite and local filesystem
  - No external API calls or cloud services during recipe capture or retrieval
  - Recipe capture must not block agent execution — use async background processing
  - Recipe schema must be backward compatible — new fields are additive only
  - System must complete recipe capture within 500ms to avoid latency impact
  - Maximum recipe size must not exceed 1MB to ensure fast retrieval
  - System must support offline operation — no network dependency
  - Recipe IDs must be globally unique across all agent instances (use UUID v4)

acceptance_criteria:
  - Given agent run data, system produces valid recipe artifact within 100ms
  - Given valid recipe, system stores it in SQLite with full-text index
  - Given recipe ID, system retrieves complete recipe with all metadata
  - Given recipe export request, system generates valid JSON/CSV without external dependencies
  - Given consecutive recipes, system detects drift when reasoning patterns change significantly
  - System runs on macOS, Linux, and Windows with Python 3.9+
  - All tests pass with pytest

dependencies: []
test_cases:
  - id: TC-001
    description: Capture basic recipe from agent run
    given: agent runs qwen3.5 model on classification task
    when: recipe compiler processes run data
    then: produces recipe with id, model, prompt_version, memory_version, evaluation, and outcome fields
  - id: TC-002
    description: Store recipe in SQLite
    given: valid recipe artifact
    when: system stores recipe
    then: recipe is retrievable by ID with all metadata intact
  - id: TC-003
    description: Export recipes to JSON
    given: 100 recipes in database
    when: system exports to JSON
    then: generates valid JSON file with all recipes
  - id: TC-004
    description: Detect recipe drift
    given: 50 consecutive recipes for same task
    when: system analyzes reasoning patterns
    then: reports drift when pattern changes exceed 20% threshold
  - id: TC-005
    description: Validate recipe schema
    given: recipe with missing required field
    when: system validates via GBNF grammar
    then: rejects recipe with clear error message
  - id: TC-006
    description: Capture does not block agent
    given: agent running inference
    when: recipe compiler processes data
    then: agent completes inference without added latency > 100ms
